Let's talk about inputs.

2
00:00:03.613 --> 00:00:07.605
So sometimes you wanna accept
information from your users, right?

3
00:00:07.605 --> 00:00:12.178
So you can imagine you're filling out
some sort of shipping information, right?

4
00:00:12.178 --> 00:00:15.843
So if you're trying to ship some shoes
to yourself or something like that,

5
00:00:15.843 --> 00:00:19.988
they'll have something here of like put
in your first name, and you'll put Brian.

6
00:00:19.988 --> 00:00:24.872
That particular part where you accept user
input is called, as you might imagine,

7
00:00:24.872 --> 00:00:25.651
user input.

8
00:00:25.651 --> 00:00:29.524
So these are browser inputs, it's input
that the browser provides for you.

9
00:00:29.524 --> 00:00:34.147
They'll look sometimes slightly different,
Windows ones will look a little bit

10
00:00:34.147 --> 00:00:38.846
different than Mac, cuz a lot of times
they're provided by the operating system.

11
00:00:38.846 --> 00:00:42.172
But yeah, they're very useful because
there are a bunch of these pre-built

12
00:00:42.172 --> 00:00:45.293
kind of components that allow you to
accept information from a user, and

13
00:00:45.293 --> 00:00:46.946
there's a bunch of different types.

14
00:00:46.946 --> 00:00:51.562
I always say the one that I 99% of the
time end up using is probably this input

15
00:00:51.562 --> 00:00:52.424
type= text.

16
00:00:52.424 --> 00:00:57.423
